HEADWORD: Provine
<hw>Pro*vine"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>provingner</ets>, fr. <ets>provin</ets> a set, layer of a plant,
OF. <ets>provain</ets>, from L. <ets>propago</ets>, <ets>-aginis</ets>,
akin to <ets>propagare</ets> to propagate. See <er>Propagate</er>,
<er>Prune</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <def>To lay a stock or branch of
a vine in the ground for propagation.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

